# Storybloom — environment variables template
#
# HOW TO USE:
# 1. Copy this file to a new file named exactly ".env"   (cp .env.example .env)
# 2. Fill in only what you need (all of these are OPTIONAL — the app runs
#    on-device with no keys).
# 3. NEVER commit .env — it is gitignored. This .env.example is safe to commit.
#
# In Expo, vars must be prefixed EXPO_PUBLIC_ to be readable in app code.
#
# Storybloom v1 runs FULLY ON-DEVICE: Tesseract OCR + a local sound matcher +
# Vosk speech recognition. No cloud, no accounts, no API keys required to use it.

# OPTIONAL: override where on-device OCR downloads its Tesseract language data
# on first run (default: tessdata_best on GitHub). Handy for a mirror, or
# side-load eng/rus.traineddata into <documents>/tesseract/tessdata/ instead.
# EXPO_PUBLIC_TESSDATA_URL=https://github.com/tesseract-ocr/tessdata_best/raw/main

# OPTIONAL: only needed to (re)build the bundled sound library from Freesound
# via scripts/fetch-freesound.mjs. NOT used by the app at runtime.
# FREESOUND_API_TOKEN=your_freesound_api_key
